5. User Journey
5.1 Connection with the River â€” Flow of Memory

The installation moves in a continuous sine-wave rhythm, mirroring the river and symbolizing the flow of collective memory.

5.2 Connection with the Wall â€” Reconstructing What Once Stood

Facing the ancient city wall, the roofline references the lost tower. Visitors can visually â€œrestoreâ€ the historic architecture through perspective.

5.3 Connection with the Tower â€” Approaching Stories

When visitors step close to a unit, the winch pauses so they can observe and absorb the embedded story.

5.4 Connection with the Audience â€” Participatory Heritage

Visitors are encouraged to explore the city, rediscover relics, and upload personal storiesâ€”expanding the installation with living memory over time.

